2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper proposes a unifying construction framework for optimal ZPU matrices, which can be useful in network design and optimization. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper investigates some important properties of ZPU matrices, which can be useful in the design and analysis of algorithms that involve matrix operations. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a new concept of ZPU matrices, which can potentially be used in machine learning applications that involve matrix operations. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with multi-rate filter banks, which are commonly used in multimedia applications such as audio and video processing.
